PredictionText: The next area you create will crash.
Name: Crash Test

PredictionText: The next area you create will stall for 10 seconds.
Name: Delay Test

PredictionText: The next area you create will stall for 10 seconds then crash.
Name: Delay and Crash Test

PredictionText: You will slay Atziri, Queen of the Vaal, and gain access to her Vaults.
Name: The Queen's Vaults
FlavourText: The Red Queen holds the key to her vaults, and only death will loosen her grip.

PredictionText: You will slay a Tormented spirit that carries a unique item.
Name: The Singular Spirit
FlavourText: A life spent fleeing from the law leaves the spirit ready to escape with its newfound treasure.

PredictionText: You will encounter and slay a Rogue Exile who wears only rare items.
Name: The Wealthy Exile
FlavourText: They flee from the eyes of Oriath, coated in gold from head to toe.

PredictionText: You will encounter and slay a Rogue Exile, who calls forth a Warband.
Name: The Scout
FlavourText: One like you roams the land, but they are just the first of many.

PredictionText: You will be attacked by a Rogue Exile when opening a Strongbox.
Name: Waiting in Ambush
FlavourText: A chest of goods hides many challenges, but one goes unseen even to the wise.

PredictionText: You will slay an Undying Alchemist, and it will drop an Orb of Alchemy.
Name: The Alchemist
FlavourText: A fool tries to turn lead to gold, but a deft hand takes it by force.

PredictionText: You will slay a very powerful king or queen, and it will drop a Regal Orb.
Name: A Regal Death
FlavourText: Blue blood drains from a cut-throat, and turns what it touches to gold.

PredictionText: You will slay a powerful enemy in a Vaal side area and it will drop a Vaal Orb.
Name: The Corrupt
FlavourText: To plow a field, you need a tool. To harvest grain, you need a tool. To spread corruption, you need a tool.

PredictionText: You will slay Izaro and he will drop an extra Treasure Key.
Name: The Emperor's Trove
FlavourText: Lost in his own creation, the Emperor leaves a generous parting gift for the precise.

PredictionText: You will slay a rare but powerful foe who then drops two unique items instead of one.
Name: Nemesis of Greed
FlavourText: A collector of antiquities doubles their treasures, relinquishing them only with their final breath.

PredictionText: You will encounter a powerful monster, and it will drop a unique item once slain.
Name: SHOULD NOT APPEAR
FlavourText: You shouldn't be seeing this!

PredictionText: You will slay Hillock and he will drop a powerful item.
Name: The Blacksmith
FlavourText: Long ago, a master of metal, now a shaper of fear. But his greatest tools remain.

PredictionText: You will kill a foe possessed by a Tormented Spirit, freeing the spirit.
Name: Forceful Exorcism
FlavourText: A pained spirit hijacks a body, and will not be stopped by that body's demise.

PredictionText: You will enter a certain map, and when you slay the very powerful foe that has made it its home, it will drop a rare map.
Name: The Dreamer's Dream
FlavourText: The greatest threat, deep in dream, holds the key to another world.

PredictionText: You will find the tormented spirit of Shavronne near Brutus. You will slay Brutus while he is possessed by her spirit.
Name: The Aesthete's Spirit
FlavourText: The echo of the Aesthete haunts her greatest creation, bestowing great powers once more.

PredictionText: You will encounter Brutus and Kole deep in Axiom Prison, and slay them both.
Name: Brothers in Arms
FlavourText: Two men, transformed into monsters, fight together to hold the gate.

PredictionText: You will travel to the stone circle in the Western Forest, and destroy the Echo of Doedre Darktongue who waits there.
Name: Echoes of Witchcraft
FlavourText: A circle of silent giants imprisons a memory of undying misery. A dark tongue whispers dark words carried by the western winds.

PredictionText: You will destroy the false idols Kuduku and Kadaka
Name: The God of Misfortune
FlavourText: Pagan mouths worship pagan gods; false idols for false promises.

PredictionText: You will find the Echo of Maligaro in the Chamber of Sins and destroy it.
Name: Echoes of Mutation
FlavourText: Perverse loyalty, blind love, the abuser and the abused reunited in sin.

PredictionText: You will find the Echo of Daresso in the Cavern of Anger and destroy it.
Name: Echoes of Lost Love
FlavourText: Twisted by temptation, tempted by corruption, the Siren's song finally calls forth a fragment of her lost love.

PredictionText: You will find Einhar and complete his mission.
Name: A Master Seeks Help
FlavourText: Prognosticating impending doom, a master survivalist seeks aid.

PredictionText: You will find Einhar and complete his mission.
Name: A Master Seeks Help
FlavourText: Prognosticating impending doom, a master survivalist seeks aid.

PredictionText: You will find Alva and complete her mission.
Name: A Master Seeks Help
FlavourText: Blind to all but gold, a master treasure hunter seeks aid.

PredictionText: You will find Alva and complete her mission.
Name: A Master Seeks Help
FlavourText: Blind to all but gold, a master treasure hunter seeks aid.

PredictionText: You will find Niko and complete his mission.
Name: A Master Seeks Help
FlavourText: Maniacally digging in endless darkness, a master miner seeks aid.

PredictionText: You will find Niko and complete his mission.
Name: A Master Seeks Help
FlavourText: Maniacally digging in endless darkness, a master miner seeks aid.

PredictionText: You will find Zana and complete her mission.
Name: A Master Seeks Help
FlavourText: Lost in the miasma of dream, a master of many realms seeks aid.

PredictionText: You will find Einhar and complete his mission.
Name: A Master Seeks Help
FlavourText: Prognosticating impending doom, a master survivalist seeks aid.

PredictionText: You will find Alva and complete her mission.
Name: A Master Seeks Help
FlavourText: Blind to all but gold, a master treasure hunter seeks aid.

PredictionText: You will find Niko and complete his mission.
Name: A Master Seeks Help
FlavourText: Maniacally digging in endless darkness, a master miner seeks aid.

PredictionText: You will find Jun and complete her mission.
Name: A Master Seeks Help
FlavourText: Pursuing a world of perfect balance, a veiled master seeks aid.

PredictionText: You will enter a hidden Vaal area that contains powerful enemies.
Name: Hidden Vaal Pathways
FlavourText: Ancient foes open new paths to the land they left barren.

PredictionText: You will seek out and destroy a group of seven powerful undead.
Name: The Undead Brutes
FlavourText: Powerful soldiers of a forgotten time reunite and march once again.

PredictionText: You will enter a map that holds four additional Rogue Exiles.
Name: The Four Feral Exiles
FlavourText: In a faraway dream, four souls far from home prepare to fight to the death.

PredictionText: You will kill a powerful monster, whose blood takes on a new form.
Name: Risen Blood
FlavourText: Life flows through the blood. Let slip the blood, and the life will continue in a new form.

PredictionText: You will trade five unique items with a vendor.
Name: The Mysterious Gift
FlavourText: A merchant seeks to trade misfitting gifts. Five for one, but what is the one?

PredictionText: You will receive an extra Chaos Orb from a vendor when you trade items that would result in a Chaos Orb.
Name: A Valuable Combination
FlavourText: When the sum is already greater than the parts, there is room to make it greater still.

PredictionText: You will create a fully-linked six-socket item using only Jeweller's Orbs.
Name: Fated Connections
FlavourText: Five and fewer stand alone, but six draws them together.

PredictionText: You will turn a normal item into a unique item with a single Chance Orb.
Name: Trash to Treasure
FlavourText: A blank canvas holds untold potential, but the artist's fortunate hand transforms it into a masterpiece.

PredictionText: You will create a fully-linked five-socket item with a single Jeweller's Orb
Name: The Jeweller's Touch
FlavourText: The Jeweller leaves five fingerprints and connects them with a single thread.

PredictionText: You will complete a Master's mission and will receive triple favour.
Name: A Gracious Master
FlavourText: A desperate ally seeks your aid, and will lavish you with appreciation.

PredictionText: You will discover a 20% quality gem.
Name: Erasmus' Gift
FlavourText: The kind gemcutter scattered his beautiful craft for the paupers, but greedy hands hide them.

PredictionText: You will defeat Kaom while holding Kaom's Sign.
Name: The King's Path
FlavourText: Madness feeds the King's fury in the raging mouth of the volcano. His last vision will be a sign.

PredictionText: You will defeat the Gemling Legionnaires while holding Karui Ward.
Name: The Karui Rebellion
FlavourText: Thaumaturgy and faith clash among giant ruins; a recreation of a long-gone rebellion.

PredictionText: You will defeat Daresso while holding Bramblejack.
Name: The King and the Brambles
FlavourText: The Blade King's blood feeds brambles that grow ever thicker.

PredictionText: You will defeat Shavronne while holding Shavronne's Pace.
Name: The Flow of Energy
FlavourText: The Aesthete sustains herself in unnatural ways. When movement fails, energy flows.

PredictionText: You will defeat Nightwane while holding Death's Harp.
Name: The Bowstring's Music
FlavourText: The brittle archer's bow plays a song of death, but the harp sings a sweet masterpiece.

PredictionText: You will defeat Bameth while holding Blackheart.
Name: From The Void
FlavourText: The iron heart, burned in the blackness of the void that lies beyond sight, rots all it touches.

PredictionText: You will defeat Gneiss while holding Craghead
Name: Heavy Blows
FlavourText: Living stone strides across the field, each step shakes the earth and rattles the soul.

PredictionText: You will defeat Hatebeat while holding Blackgleam.
Name: Fire and Brimstone
FlavourText: Living cinders set the stone alight, a gleaming signal in the blackness where husks are burned.

PredictionText: You will defeat Torchoak Grove while holding Araku Tiki.
Name: A Forest of False Idols
FlavourText: A grove of wooden faces spit fire, a cheap mockery of unimaginable power.

PredictionText: You will defeat Hailrake while holding Hrimsorrow.
Name: Fire and Ice
FlavourText: Cold sorrow turns to burning fury that hails across the shattered ship.

PredictionText: You will defeat Shavronne while holding Crown of Thorns.
Name: Pleasure and Pain
FlavourText: A single thorn slips through stretched skin; pain turns to power.

PredictionText: You will defeat the Gemling Legionnaires while holding Ezomyte Peak
Name: The Bloody Flowers Redux
FlavourText: Ezomyte banners flutter through the air as embellished monsters fall, a reenactment of the slave's final victory.

PredictionText: You will defeat General Gravicius while holding Deidbell.
Name: Dying Cry
FlavourText: The bell tolls, the people gather, the General is executed. The militia cries out and charges forth.

PredictionText: You will defeat Doedre while holding Chalice of Horrors.
Name: Mouth of Horrors
FlavourText: The vile witch whispers words of horror, and sups from the chalice one final time.

PredictionText: You will defeat Calaf, Headstaver while holding Springleaf.
Name: Nature's Resilience
FlavourText: Thieves camp beneath roadside trees, but it is their leader who falls like the mighty oak.

PredictionText: You will defeat Chatters while holding Kaltenhalt.
Name: The Snuffed Flame
FlavourText: Cold bones rattle in stone cells, extinguishing all light, all warmth, all hope.

PredictionText: You will defeat the Hundred Foot Shadow while holding Screaming Eagle.
Name: The Apex Predator
FlavourText: The eagle battles the vulture in the shadow of a dying sun, and becomes something greater.

PredictionText: You will defeat Hammerstorm while holding Limbsplit.
Name: Severed Limbs
FlavourText: A storm of stone stops when the last of the limbs are severed and blood flows no more.

PredictionText: You will defeat the Vaal Oversoul while holding Doomfletch.
Name: Ancient Doom
FlavourText: Doom grows at the apex of the pyramid.

PredictionText: You will defeat Targa, Beast Poacher while holding Silverbranch.
Name: The Silverwood
FlavourText: A thief, bow in hand, flees to the wooded outskirts.

PredictionText: You will defeat Fidelitas while holding Storm Cloud.
Name: The Servant's Heart
FlavourText: The Servant's sacrifice summons a storm in the Prodigy's soul.

PredictionText: You will defeat Soulmourn while holding Hrimnor's Hymn
Name: Winter's Mournful Melodies
FlavourText: A mournful hymn, a mournful soul, the chill of death on the wind.

PredictionText: You will defeat Piety while holding Reverberation Rod
Name: Power Magnified
FlavourText: The pious grow powerful surrounded by a sea of blood and empty husks

PredictionText: You will defeat Archbishop Geofri while holding Realmshaper.
Name: The Beginning and the End
FlavourText: The archbishop plays witness to his own cold death and cremation.

PredictionText: You will defeat the Bone Queen while holding Queen's Decree.
Name: The Misunderstood Queen
FlavourText: A queen of bone raises an army and flees among walls of flesh.

PredictionText: All normal monsters in area become magic - NOTE: Currently very laggy, do not enable
Name: SHOULD NOT APPEAR
FlavourText: You shouldn't be seeing this!

PredictionText: You will use an Orb of Transmutation on an Onyx Amulet, applying elemental resistances.
Name: The Black Stone I
FlavourText: The black stone senses resilience in you. It too grows resilient to outside influences.

PredictionText: You will use an Orb of Augmentation on the Onyx Amulet, applying life.
Name: The Black Stone II
FlavourText: The black stone senses the joy of life in you. It feeds on this joy and grows more lively.

PredictionText: You will use a Regal Orb on the Onyx Amulet, applying critical strike chance.
Name: The Black Stone III
FlavourText: The black stone senses eagerness in you. It longs for the excitement of combat, of bloodshed.

PredictionText: You will use an Exalted Orb on the Onyx Amulet, turning it into a powerful new item.
Name: The Black Stone IV
FlavourText: The black stone learns from you. It is ready to shape each encounter in your favour.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Ruined Titan who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Walking Mountain
FlavourText: Shaped by magic, the tool that breathes life into the titan's stone lies at its heart.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Axiom Thunderguard who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Prison Guard
FlavourText: Clad in black, the guard holds the key to unleashing the storm.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Mad Gladiator who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Sword King's Passion
FlavourText: Once a challenger to the crown, he holds in his hands the Sword King's blade.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Murk Runner who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Eagle's Cry
FlavourText: A flightless fowl charges through rotten wooden ribs; its scream gives even the battle-hardened pause.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Dripping Dead who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: From Death Springs Life
FlavourText: Fetid waters carry the dead downstream, but walking in the mud, the dead one carries life.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Brittle Poacher who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Storm on the Horizon
FlavourText: The poacher's bowstring snaps like dry bone and crackles like thunder.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Seething Brine who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: A Firm Foothold
FlavourText: Water slicks the stone, a misstep chills the bone, the living pools hold the cure.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Bearded Shaman who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Ward's Ward
FlavourText: The false shaman's death uncovers ancestral allurement locked in ancient stone.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Devourer who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Fear's Wide Reach
FlavourText: The unseen enemy travels through unseen tunnels. Its reach is small, but its effect is large.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Bearded Devil who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Prison Key
FlavourText: The gate is unlocked, but the key remains in the hands of a devil.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Oak's Devoted who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Roth's Legacy
FlavourText: The devotee holds a relic of the pirate's past, looted and lost for an age.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Ancient Construct who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Soulless Beast
FlavourText: Powered by twin wings, the mechanical monster roams the ruins.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Sin Lord who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Sinner's Stone
FlavourText: A lord of sin roams hollow halls protected from the spells he sings.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Death Bishop who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Baptism by Death
FlavourText: The bishop's flock is long gone, yet still he wields his hefty crook.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Blackguard Arcmage who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Lady in Black
FlavourText: Lightning's hum grows louder and louder in the hands of the lady in black.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Dockhand Wraith who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Against the Tide
FlavourText: Taken by the fickle tides, the Captain's bow washes against the dock from which he set sail.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Blackguard Elite who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Brutal Enforcer
FlavourText: In a society that values violence, the violent rise through the ranks like oil through water.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Flame Sentinel who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Graceful Flames
FlavourText: Crimson fabric flutters with fury and flame, but a gilded prize lies within.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Brine Vassal who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Storm on the Reef
FlavourText: Lightning flashes overhead. Bloated bodies wash ashore. One stands, walks, and stretches its wing.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Pocked Lanternbearer who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Petrified
FlavourText: Lightless halls hewn in stone swell with the malformed, the twisted, the hardened and the dangerous.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Voll's Vanguard who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Vanguard
FlavourText: The Vanguard lead the funereal march, playing hymns of death with their bowstrings.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Undying Evangelist who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Cleanser of Sins
FlavourText: The Evangelist does not practise what he preaches, but death wipes clean the slate.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Fighting Bull who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Strong as a Bull
FlavourText: Strength to rival the Karui King charges through the Sword King's dream.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Skulking Dweller who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Lost Undying
FlavourText: Trapped with his emperor when the crown was taken, he seeks to change his fate.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Frost Preacher who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: A Whispered Prayer
FlavourText: A preacher whispers to the skies and the skies answer with a blanket of biting frost.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Ancient Archer who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Last Watch
FlavourText: A loyal soldier in life, he stands watch, bow in hand, waiting to be sent to the Mother of death.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Sutured Aberration who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: A Prodigious Hand
FlavourText: The dead one brought back to life by means other than corruption now holds the hands that revived it.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Wandering Eye who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Watcher's Watcher
FlavourText: Unblinking, it watches. Unendingly, it is watched.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Kaom's Chosen in a map who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Blood of the Betrayed
FlavourText: Slain by their king, they live only in memory, but their lust for blood remains unsated.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Solar Guard who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Heart of the Fire
FlavourText: Its one desire is to see the world burn. A shard of fury stokes the undying fire in its heart.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Pocked Mason who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Notched Flesh
FlavourText: Stiff is the bow. Brittle is the flesh that holds it. Deep are the holes it leaves.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Assault Ribbon who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Custodians of Silence
FlavourText: The temple untouched for centuries, the guardians clean and pure, yet they too must meet the Mother.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Bonewarped Warrior who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Flesh of the Beast
FlavourText: Stripped of its flesh, a warrior fights to protect the piece of the beast it has carved.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Cinder Elemental in a map who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Fire, Wood and Stone
FlavourText: With crushing weight, the stone figure roams the halls. It burns eternally yet grows no lighter.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Chaos Sentinel in a map who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Abnormal Effulgence
FlavourText: Living stone and effulgence, nothing moves unhindered beneath the weight of its dark presence.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Galvanic Ribbon in a map who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Wind and Thunder
FlavourText: The dreaming fabric flutters and cracks in the wind like thunder. A sharp sound that freezes the blood.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Undying Archivist in a map who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Lost in the Pages
FlavourText: Hundreds of years with nothing but books twists a once great mind.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Dripping Dead in a map who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Weeping Death
FlavourText: Striding dryly through the mud, yet dripping with rot, he waits for the Mother's touch.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Gut Flayer in a map who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Flayed Man
FlavourText: The flayed becomes the flayer, stripping flesh from muscle with a sharpened edge.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Tunneler in a map who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Hollow Pledge
FlavourText: Grasping blindly through a dark dream, a final pledge turns brittle flesh to dust.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Talon Archer in a map who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: A Call into the Void
FlavourText: The dreaming cockerel crows thrice, and thunder bellows from the void.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Mad Gladiator in a map who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: Blood in the Eyes
FlavourText: Blood stains the fighter's eyes and rains upon the dirt. He sees and dreams in crimson.

PredictionText: You will track down a powerful Noxious Tarantula in a map who will drop a unique item when slain.
Name: The Nest
FlavourText: Rats become tangled in the spider's web; a meal within a nest within a dream.

PredictionText: You will encounter four necromancers with their undead minions and slay them all.
Name: The Brothers of Necromancy
FlavourText: Four of shared flesh and blood raise an army of borrowed blood and bone.

PredictionText: You will end a Bloodline.
Name: Reforged Bonds
FlavourText: A bond of blood breaks, but from the carnage new bonds may be formed.

PredictionText: You will slay a foe who erupts into currency.
Name: Overflowing Riches
FlavourText: A full pocket, severed, spills forth like a struck spring.

PredictionText: You will encounter a powerful golem in a Vaal side area and defeat it.
Name: The Plaguemaw I
FlavourText: The Plaguemaw enters the red realm and leaves a swirling mass of living stone.

PredictionText: You will encounter shadowy monsters in the Crypt and slay them.
Name: The Plaguemaw II
FlavourText: The Plaguemaw's followers feed on the flesh of the dead; a desecration of the Mother's work.
PredictionText2: You will encounter shadowy monsters in the Crypt, Bone Crypt Map, Cursed Crypt Map, or Necropolis Map and slay them.

PredictionText: You will be ambushed by the Plaguemaw's followers after you kill a certain very powerful monster.
Name: The Plaguemaw III
FlavourText: The Plaguemaw watches you with a glistening grin, waiting for a moment to send his shadows.

PredictionText: You will be ambushed by the Plaguemaw's followers in the Imperial Gardens.
Name: The Plaguemaw IV
FlavourText: In a maze of green, the Plaguemaw sets a trap baited with treasures.
PredictionText2: You will be ambushed by the Plaguemaw's followers in the Imperial Gardens, Gardens Map, Courtyard Map, or Orchard Map.

PredictionText: You will enter the Plaguemaw's chamber in the Crystal Veins.
Name: The Plaguemaw V
FlavourText: A room, etched in crystal, plays home to the Plaguemaw. He awaits you.
PredictionText2: You will enter the Plaguemaw's chamber in the Crystal Veins or Crystal Ore Map.

PredictionText: You will read Shavronne's Journal in the Warden's Quarters.
Name: Thaumaturgical History I
FlavourText: The Aesthete's monstrous techniques are protected by the shadows.

PredictionText: You will read Doedre's Proclamation in The Western Forest in Act 2.
Name: Thaumaturgical History II
FlavourText: The Tongueless Witch's words speak through the stone to desperate followers.

PredictionText: You will inspect the Ancient Reverie Device in the Chamber of Sins.
Name: Thaumaturgical History III
FlavourText: The Soulless One's gift to the Prodigy draws forth those who seek the same unnatural power.

PredictionText: You will read Malachai's Dedication in The Harvest.
Name: Thaumaturgical History IV
FlavourText: Where the Soulless One left his physical form behind, a dangerous new threat emerges.

PredictionText: You will slay Belcer, the Pirate Lord, and he will open portals to Mao Kun.
Name: The Pirate's Den
FlavourText: The pirate lord who hides in dank tunnels deep in dream will guide you to an island of treasure.

PredictionText: You will slay Void Anomaly and he will open portals to Maelström of Chaos.
Name: Enter the Maelström
FlavourText: The swirling mass of dark stone stands at the centre of the dreaming storm.

PredictionText: You will slay The Idol Beyond and he will open portals to Olmec's Sanctum
Name: Sanctum of Stone
FlavourText: Break apart the wooden god, and a door to the stone sanctum appears.

PredictionText: You will slay Mirage of Bones and he will open portals to a mirror world.
Name: Through the Mirage
FlavourText: Washing away the mirage unveils a parallel path to walk.

PredictionText: You will slay Brutus while wearing one of Shavronne's items.
Name: Ancient Rivalries I
FlavourText: Her greatest creation failed her. The Aesthete seeks to punish the brute.

PredictionText: You will slay Voll while wearing one of Doedre's items.
Name: Ancient Rivalries II
FlavourText: Burned at the stake, the Tongueless Witch seeks to purify the purifier.

PredictionText: You will slay Kaom while wearing one of Lioneye's items.
Name: Ancient Rivalries III
FlavourText: Cut down on the shores, the Lion's fangs will sink into the Betraying King's flesh one last time.

PredictionText: You will slay Malachai while wearing one of Victario's items.
Name: Ancient Rivalries IV
FlavourText: The Soulless One tore the world asunder, but the Poet will have the final word.

PredictionText: You will encounter corrupted animals in the Southern Forest and slay them.
Name: The Feral Lord I
FlavourText: The Feral Lord in the southern wood twists the wild to his will.
PredictionText2: You will encounter corrupted animals in the Southern Forest or Tropical Island Map and slay them.

PredictionText: You will encounter a powerful beast in the Northern Forest and slay it.
Name: The Feral Lord II
FlavourText: The Feral Lord's cold breath imbues and empowers the beast in the northern wood.
PredictionText2: You will encounter a powerful beast in the Northern Forest, Jungle Valley Map, or Dark Forest Map and slay it.

PredictionText: You will encounter corrupted animals in the Dried Lake and slay them.
Name: The Feral Lord III
FlavourText: Where water shimmers no more, thunderous beasts are dragged into the Feral Lord's domain.
PredictionText2: You will encounter corrupted animals in the Dried Lake, Desert Map, or Wasteland Map and slay them.

PredictionText: You will discover and slay a very powerful Vulture within Sarn's borders.
Name: The Feral Lord IV
FlavourText: The Feral Lord senses your presence. In the shell of the snail, the vulture seeks a fresh carcass.
PredictionText2: You will discover and slay a very powerful Vulture within Sarn's borders or Maps of Sarn.

PredictionText: You will discover and slay a very powerful fiery Rhoa in a Mud Geyser map.
Name: The Feral Lord V
FlavourText: To the realm of dreams the Feral Lord flees, and leaves in his wake a burning nightmare.

PredictionText: You will discover a series of indoor chambers flooded with rats.
Name: Plague of Rats
FlavourText: They run, they bite, they flee, they die. Swarms of fur and teeth and tail drown each and every room.

PredictionText: You will enter a map and slay a Rogue Exile who is carrying a Divination Card.
Name: Anarchy's End I
FlavourText: A criminal of Theopolis flees into dream carrying a fortuneteller's tool.

PredictionText: You will enter a map and slay two Rogue Exiles who are each carrying a Divination Card.
Name: Anarchy's End II
FlavourText: Two criminals carry the fortuneteller's tools as they hunt for the body of their dreaming ally.

PredictionText: You will enter a map and slay four Rogue Exiles who are each carrying a Divination Card.
Name: Anarchy's End III
FlavourText: A party of four criminals, each with the mark of the fortuneteller, hunt through dreams for their prosecutor.

PredictionText: You will enter a map and slay six Rogue Exiles who are each carrying a Divination Card.
Name: Anarchy's End IV
FlavourText: Six criminals take to foot to stamp out the threat that tracks them through dreams.

PredictionText: You will be rewarded with an additional use of the Divine Font on completing the Labyrinth.
Name: Twice Enchanted
FlavourText: A golden device hidden by a rotting emperor overflows with power.

PredictionText: You will be attacked by stronger than normal monsters when opening a Strongbox.
Name: An Unseen Peril
FlavourText: A trap is set, a lure is placed, but stronger foes lie in wait.

PredictionText: You will find and destroy monsters from Beyond who are trying to invade Wraeclast through the map device.
Name: Mysterious Invaders
FlavourText: Beyond the golden gears, the edges of reality crack, and something hidden from sight spills through.

PredictionText: You will find and destroy monsters from Beyond who are trying to invade Wraeclast through the map device.
Name: Mysterious Invaders
FlavourText: Beyond the golden gears, the edges of reality crack, and something hidden from sight spills through.

PredictionText: You will find and destroy monsters from Beyond who are trying to invade Wraeclast through the map device.
Name: Mysterious Invaders
FlavourText: Beyond the golden gears, the edges of reality crack, and something hidden from sight spills through.

PredictionText: You will find and destroy monsters from Beyond who are trying to invade Wraeclast through the map device.
Name: Mysterious Invaders
FlavourText: Beyond the golden gears, the edges of reality crack, and something hidden from sight spills through.

PredictionText: You will find and destroy monsters from Beyond who are trying to invade Wraeclast through the map device.
Name: Mysterious Invaders
FlavourText: Beyond the golden gears, the edges of reality crack, and something hidden from sight spills through.

PredictionText: You will travel to the Old Fields, where you will encounter and slay an army of the undead.
Name: Undead Uprising
FlavourText: The green and verdant field is swathed in night, the farmers who tended to it rise again.

PredictionText: You will slay a powerful Vaal Fallen who will drop a Sacrifice at Dawn fragment.
Name: Day of Sacrifice I
FlavourText: The ancient red champion is fallen, but a killing blow reveals his final sacrifice beneath the morning sun.

PredictionText: You will open a corrupted rare strongbox that will contain a Sacrifice at Noon fragment.
Name: Day of Sacrifice II
FlavourText: Beneath the midday sun, treasure, stained by corruption, invites an ambush.

PredictionText: You will enter a difficult Vaal side area that contains an additional Sacrifice at Dusk fragment.
Name: Day of Sacrifice III
FlavourText: The ancient red army opens a powerful path before the setting sun.

PredictionText: You will encounter an invading foe in a rare, corrupted map, who will drop a Sacrifice at Midnight fragment.
Name: Day of Sacrifice IV
FlavourText: A corrupted dream invites an invader, who hunts in the deepest night.

PredictionText: You will slay a powerful foe, and gain a shrine's blessing.
Name: The Blessing
FlavourText: Malevolence swells and spreads in minds. The flesh is weak, but the gift is strong.

PredictionText: You will slay a powerful foe and gain its powers.
Name: Hunter's Lesson
FlavourText: An adversary, slain, briefly lives on in the lessons taught to the slayer.

PredictionText: You will slay a powerful foe and it will drop a rare item.
Name: Gilded Within
FlavourText: Gold without, gold within. Blood comes in many colours, but the gilded always bleed gold.

PredictionText: You will slay a very powerful foe and it will drop an Orb of Scouring.
Name: Erased from Memory
FlavourText: A foe feared for an aeon falls and is scoured from the pages of history.

PredictionText: You will slay a powerful foe who will release a Tormented Spirit.
Name: Ending the Torment
FlavourText: A fearsome foe's inner torment spills out into the world.

PredictionText: You will be ambushed by several enemies upon slaying a foe.
Name: Hidden Reinforcements
FlavourText: Cowardly foes lay in wait. A show of force reveals their true intentions.

PredictionText: You will slay a normal foe, who will be resurrected and granted new power.
Name: Rebirth
FlavourText: An ordinary life, an ordinary death, marked by an extraordinary rebirth.

PredictionText: You will greatly enhance the quality of a weapon with a single Blacksmith's Whetstone.
Name: The Sharpened Blade
FlavourText: The metal softens beneath the stone, reshaping with great ease.

PredictionText: You will greatly enhance the quality of an armour piece with a single Armourer's Scrap
Name: The Hardened Armour
FlavourText: The rings that bind grow tighter, the plate thicker, the leather denser, all with a single touch.

PredictionText: You will use an Orb of Transmutation on an item and it will grant extra mods.
Name: Golden Touch
FlavourText: Blue tendrils entangle and change. All that remains is gold.

PredictionText: You will use an Orb of Transmutation on a ring or amulet and it will gain a life mod.
Name: Vital Transformation
FlavourText: Blue tendrils envelop, breathing life into the beautifully inert.

PredictionText: You will use an Orb of Transmutation on a ring, shield, or amulet, and it will gain resistances.
Name: Resistant to Change
FlavourText: Wreathed in blue sinew, it is protected from the flames, the storms and the snow alike.

PredictionText: You will use an Orb of Transmutation on a pair of boots and it will gain movement speed.
Name: Touched by the Wind
FlavourText: Stitched with blue thread, a swift boot covers great distances.

PredictionText: You will slay a foe and it will drop two Divination cards.
Name: The Pair
FlavourText: One carries the fortune teller's mark, not knowing that a second surprise lies with it.

PredictionText: You will greatly enhance the quality of a map with a single Cartographer's Chisel.
Name: The Beautiful Guide
FlavourText: A single tap from the chisel, and the guide's marks grow far clearer.

PredictionText: You will slay a foe who drops four identical rare items.
Name: Kalandra's Craft
FlavourText: A grand treasure fractures like a dropped mirror, yet somehow goes unharmed.

PredictionText: You will use an Orb of Transmutation on a map and it will gain a smothering atmosphere.
Name: Smothering Tendrils
FlavourText: Blue tendrils wrap around the markings, constricting and smothering the stone beneath.

PredictionText: You will enter a map that holds six additional Strongboxes.
Name: Bountiful Traps
FlavourText: In a distant dream, six traps with the promise of treasure wait to be sprung.

PredictionText: You will find four Rogue Exiles in a map and slay them.
Name: The Four Feral Exiles
FlavourText: In a faraway dream, four souls far from home prepare to fight to the death.

PredictionText: You will enter a map and slay the Twinned bosses in it.
Name: Deadly Twins
FlavourText: In a long-lost dream, one deadly foe becomes two.

PredictionText: You will read something written long ago.
Name: Lasting Impressions
FlavourText: A hand scrawls on a wall, or carves into bone, a tale that undoes the world and teaches those who come after.

PredictionText: You will discover an area with an Infernal Tempest
Name: Fire from the Sky
FlavourText: Fire rains down across the land. Beware the path you take.

PredictionText: You will discover an area with an Arctic Tempest
Name: Ice from Above
FlavourText: The cold blusters from above, chilling the unwary to the bone.

PredictionText: You will discover an area with an Electrocuting Tempest
Name: Lightning Falls
FlavourText: The storms above strike with precision. A deft foot will avoid the blows.

PredictionText: You will discover an area with a Morbid Tempest
Name: The Undead Storm
FlavourText: Bones fall from the sky and take the shape of the men they once were.

PredictionText: You will discover an area with a Crushing Tempest
Name: Crushing Squall
FlavourText: The sky trembles and the ground below answers with crushing force.

PredictionText: You will discover an area with a Corrupting Tempest
Name: Vaal Winds
FlavourText: Corruption is carried on a red wind, and spreads to all who are touched.

PredictionText: You will discover a powerful fire golem at Fire Fury's camp in The Coast.
Name: Living Fires
FlavourText: Where the sand meets the water, the flesheater's flames shine brighter and brighter still.

PredictionText: You will fight waves of risen farmers amongst the ruins of a house in Crossroads.
Name: Fallow At Last
FlavourText: The farmer's time came long ago, his ruined home the site of a dark harvest.

PredictionText: You will encounter Karui Spirits near Weathered Carvings, and send them back to Hinekora.
Name: Path of Betrayal
FlavourText: Cut down by the king's hand, southern spirits linger near the bones of giants.

PredictionText: You will encounter the risen weapons of a fallen army around Lioneye's Standard in The Climb.
Name: The Forgotten Soldiers
FlavourText: The banner in the breeze marks the resting place of lions, whose metal fangs still thirst for blood.

PredictionText: You will encounter and slay golden elementals deep in the Cavern of Anger.
Name: Pools of Wealth
FlavourText: Beckoned by the Siren's song, wrathful gold rises from the ground.

PredictionText: Near the Crossroads, you will encounter the Child of Lunaris in the ruins of a temple, and slay it.
Name: The Child of Lunaris
FlavourText: The light of Lunaris shines on her child who walks in stone shrine's ruins.

PredictionText: Near the Broken Bridge, you will encounter and slay an army of undead in the ruins of the fortress.
Name: The Forgotten Garrison
FlavourText: Where bandits have taken hold, a lifeless army rises to guard the ruined fortress.

PredictionText: You will encounter the Stockkeeper at the Grain Gate and slay him.
Name: The Stockkeeper
FlavourText: A man survives only by his greed, but a single weapon cuts down the man who has many.

PredictionText: You will encounter a powerful Lightning Elemental near the Battlefront bridge.
Name: Unnatural Energy
FlavourText: Unnatural energies hold those in black at bay, but the barrier bends for crackling kin.

PredictionText: You will encounter and slay two powerful Blackguard captains near the Ebony Barracks bridge.
Name: Holding the Bridge
FlavourText: Where those in black swarm across the stone steps, one's blood runs cold with hatred and one's eyes crackle with wrath.

PredictionText: You will encounter a powerful undead Blackguard in the Imperial Gardens.
Name: In the Grasp of Corruption
FlavourText: A soldier in black's journey is cut short at the foot of the tower. The flesh rots, but the bone grows yet.

PredictionText: You will encounter a group of strong miscreations in the Upper Sceptre of God, and slay them all.
Name: Defiled in the Sceptre
FlavourText: Stolen from their homes, innocent flesh is twisted and shaped atop the tower.

PredictionText: You will find maps near the centre of the Chamber of Sins.
Name: The Lost Maps
FlavourText: A device of great power once held by the prodigy spills forth the keys to new worlds.

PredictionText: You will encounter an area where powerful monsters are duplicated.
Name: The Twins
FlavourText: What was one is now two. The strong find greater strength in numbers.

PredictionText: You will encounter one or more very powerful monsters possessed by a Tormented Spirit.
Name: Possessed Foe
FlavourText: A name remembered all this time, their will stolen by a vengeful spirit.

PredictionText: You will kill a Tormented Spirit who then touches all other monsters. - NOTE: Currently very laggy
Name: Touched by Death
FlavourText: A tormented soul makes one final grasp at vengeance.

PredictionText: You will find Vaal invaders in the Temple of Lunaris and destroy the monster who is leading them.
Name: Vaal Invasion
FlavourText: At the site of a great atrocity, the shadows of the distant past hang over the risen red army.

PredictionText: You will travel to a map where the monsters lie in wait, open the boxes they guard, and slay them all.
Name: Monstrous Treasure
FlavourText: In a long lost dream, great foes hide in tiny boxes, but so do great rewards.

PredictionText: You will find and cleanse a location where the corruption of the Vaal has spread.
Name: The Spread of Corruption
FlavourText: Corruption spreads thick and fast, so too do those who revere it.

PredictionText: You will discover an outdoor location flooded with frogs.
Name: Plague of Frogs
FlavourText: Wet and slippery flesh, clinging feet and tongue. No matter the colour before, now the earth is green.

PredictionText: You will find an area littered with the drowned.
Name: Visions of the Drowned
FlavourText: Damp and bloated with water and goods. Sometimes treasure washes ashore.

PredictionText: You will discover a Trial of Ascendancy in a map.
Name: The Dream Trial
FlavourText: The depths of a dream hide a gauntlet that sharpens the body and mind.

PredictionText: You will discover an area with large packs of Undead monsters.
Name: Soil, Worms and Blood
FlavourText: The unliving crowd into the dwellings of unlikely allies.

PredictionText: You will discover an area with large packs of Insects.
Name: The Hungering Swarm
FlavourText: Skittering across the ground, insects nest near unlikely allies.

PredictionText: You will discover an area with large packs of Sea Witches.
Name: The Cursed Choir
FlavourText: The sea witch whispers sweet nothings, and calms the hearts of unlikely allies.

PredictionText: You will discover an area with many Devourers.
Name: The Trembling Earth
FlavourText: The earth shifts beneath the feet of many, but they are not the prey this monster seeks.

PredictionText: You will encounter a very powerful invading monster and slay it.
Name: The Invader
FlavourText: A horror from the past returns to cause pain in a place that it never called home.

PredictionText: You will discover a tome in the Library.
Name: Unbearable Whispers I
FlavourText: Dark runes skitter across the pages of the tome, concealing the Whisperer's allies.
PredictionText2: You will discover a tome in the Library, Academy Map, Museum Map, or Scriptorium Map.

PredictionText: You will discover a tome upon slaying a monster in the Sceptre of God.
Name: Unbearable Whispers II
FlavourText: The Whisperer leaves a tome in the tower, held by a maddened follower.
PredictionText2: You will discover a tome upon slaying a monster in the Sceptre of God, Palace Map, Residence Map, or Villa Map.

PredictionText: You will slay Shavronne, and she will drop a tome.
Name: Unbearable Whispers III
FlavourText: The Aesthete holds the Whisperer's forbidden words safe, deep in the beast's belly.

PredictionText: You will slay a certain powerful monster and it will drop a tome.
Name: Unbearable Whispers IV
FlavourText: Forbidden words ring in the ears of the powerful; the Whisperer's influence spreads.

PredictionText: You will discover a dangerous tome in the final chamber of the Labyrinth.
Name: Unbearable Whispers V
FlavourText: The trapped emperor unknowingly protects foul knowledge. Dark pages amongst bright treasures.

PredictionText: You will encounter spectres in the Fellshrine Ruins and slay them.
Name: The Unbreathing Queen I
FlavourText: The Unbreathing Queen masterminds an unholy heist, a defilement of the dead.
PredictionText2: You will encounter spectres in the Fellshrine Ruins, Cemetery Map, or Graveyard Map and slay them.

PredictionText: You will encounter the spirit of a hero in the Lord's Labyrinth and defeat it.
Name: The Unbreathing Queen II
FlavourText: The flesh is taken by the Unbreathing Queen. But the hero's soul, bitter and cold, remains trapped in the Emperor's greatest trial.

PredictionText: You will encounter the spirit of a hero in the Beacon and defeat it
Name: The Unbreathing Queen III
FlavourText: Water crashes against stone; A victim of the Unbreathing Queen burns with desire for The Mother's domain.
PredictionText2: You will encounter the spirit of a hero in the Beacon or Lighthouse Map and defeat it.

PredictionText: You will encounter the spirit of a hero in the Temple of Decay and defeat it.
Name: The Unbreathing Queen IV
FlavourText: A tangle of web trapped the body, now stolen. The Unbreathing Queen leaves behind a sorrowful soul whose howls thunder through the halls.
PredictionText2: You will encounter the spirit of a hero in the Temple of Decay or Arachnid Tomb Map and defeat it.

PredictionText: You will defeat the Unbreathing Queen in a Cemetery map.
Name: The Unbreathing Queen V
FlavourText: The Unbreathing Queen raises an army in a dream of tombs and graves. She knows you are coming.

PredictionText: You will encounter and slay bandits in an area where they do not ordinarily appear.
Name: The Ambitious Bandit I
FlavourText: A bandit's ambition grows, and so too does the path it walks.

PredictionText: You will encounter and slay bandits in the Marketplace.
Name: The Ambitious Bandit II
FlavourText: A bandit seeks a relic for the greedy where greed was once a great virtue.
PredictionText2: You will encounter and slay bandits in the Marketplace, Arcade Map, Bazaar Map, Port Map or Alleyways Map.

PredictionText: You will encounter and slay bandits in the Library.
Name: The Ambitious Bandit III
FlavourText: Where relics and tomes gather dust, a bandit's eyes see great value.
PredictionText2: You will encounter and slay bandits in the Library, Academy Map, Museum Map, or Scriptorium Map.

PredictionText: You will encounter a rival Exile imbued with Nemesis powers.
Name: Deadly Rivalry I
FlavourText: You draw the ire of another, imbued with golden power.

PredictionText: You will encounter the rival Exile, now also imbued with Onslaught.
Name: Deadly Rivalry II
FlavourText: Their defeat will not stand, renewed and fueled by blind rage.

PredictionText: You will encounter the rival Exile, now possessed by a Tormented Spirit.
Name: Deadly Rivalry III
FlavourText: Their body broken and mended, now a conduit for a greater power.

PredictionText: You will encounter the rival Exile, now imbued with the powers of a Shrine
Name: Deadly Rivalry IV
FlavourText: Prayer at a dark altar mends torn flesh once again, but darkness still fills the soul. Each defeat feeds their determination.

PredictionText: You will encounter the rival Exile, now backed by others of a shared Bloodline.
Name: Deadly Rivalry V
FlavourText: Allies arrive for a final battle, filled with shared blood. The breaking and mending takes its toll.

PredictionText: You will encounter and slay several Warbands.
Name: The Warmongers I
FlavourText: A vanguard seeks to claim land that is not theirs.

PredictionText: You will encounter and slay several Warbands and their reinforcements.
Name: The Warmongers II
FlavourText: The vanguard did not return, so more have followed their path, bringing war with them.

PredictionText: You will encounter and slay several Warbands and their elite soldiers.
Name: The Warmongers III
FlavourText: Failure twice draws the ire of higher ranking soldiers. They come to spill blood.

PredictionText: You will encounter and slay several Warbands and their leader.
Name: The Warmongers IV
FlavourText: The leader arrives, and lays plans to paint the land red with your blood.

PredictionText: You will slay the cultists and the foes they summon.
Name: Beyond Sight I
FlavourText: A dark presence hides just out of sight. Only bodies betray its movements.

PredictionText: You will slay the cultists and the powerful foes they summon.
Name: Beyond Sight II
FlavourText: A visible following forms around an invisible foe. It grows greater yet remains veiled.

PredictionText: You will slay the cultists and the powerful foes they summon.
Name: Beyond Sight III
FlavourText: Monsters not of this world spill forth. Only shapes and movement. A warped vision.

PredictionText: You will slay the Herald of Bameth and the very powerful foe it summons.
Name: Beyond Sight IV
FlavourText: My vision grows dark. A horror draws near. Its soul would be a treasured prize for Hinekora.

PredictionText: You will find a chest containing Divination Cards in a map.
Name: The Fortune Teller's Collection
FlavourText: The dreaming seeker finds what a fortune teller forgets.

PredictionText: You will defeat Tsoagoth, The Brine King while holding Icetomb.
Name: End of the Light
FlavourText: The king rots in his frozen tomb, atop the island of his own creation.

PredictionText: You will defeat Guardian of the Vault while holding Wondertrap.
Name: Greed's Folly
FlavourText: A trap of greed is laid in the Vault, and sprung at its heart by a wonder.

PredictionText: You will defeat Master of the Blade while holding Briskwrap.
Name: Last of the Wildmen
FlavourText: The Master's blade strikes the ground, and his body briskly follows. The line of the Wild Men ends.

PredictionText: You will defeat Dawn, Harbinger of Solaris while holding Sundance.
Name: Sun's Punishment
FlavourText: Death's dance with dawn leads to the midday sun, whose spiteful zenith burns indiscriminately.

PredictionText: You will defeat Doedre the Defiler while holding Windscream.
Name: Darktongue's Shriek
FlavourText: Where the dead still rest, the defiler's scream bellows through the tombs before falling eternally silent.

PredictionText: You will defeat Maligaro, The Inquisitor while holding Dusktoe.
Name: Agony at Dusk
FlavourText: In the beast's belly, the Inquisitor hunts the dying light.

PredictionText: You will defeat Tore, Towering Ancient while holding Meginord's Vise.
Name: Fall of the Tower
FlavourText: The ancient tower stands for now, but crumbles beneath a strong hand.

PredictionText: You will defeat Erythrophagia while holding Doedre's Tenure.
Name: The Malevolent Witch
FlavourText: Silence and darkness harbour growing malevolence as the blood eater meets her maker.

PredictionText: You will defeat Sumter the Twisted while holding Heatshiver.
Name: A Vision of Ice and Fire
FlavourText: Where the river meets the sea, the flames meet winter's chill, and heated battle sends a shiver down a twisted spine.

PredictionText: You will defeat Riftwalker while holding Timeclasp.
Name: A Rift in Time
FlavourText: The rift is torn open, and time's clasp is twisted.

PredictionText: You will defeat Atziri, Queen of the Vaal in the Alluring Abyss while holding Atziri's Mirror.
Name: The Queen's Sacrifice
FlavourText: The ancient queen casts her gaze upon her reflection, and at last the curse is broken.

PredictionText: You will defeat Shadow of the Vaal while holding Quecholli.
Name: The Fall of an Empire
FlavourText: The Vaal's dark machinery was their greatest triumph, and its destruction another's destiny.

PredictionText: You will defeat Caliga, Imperatrix while holding Fencoil.
Name: Trapped in the Tower
FlavourText: The Imperatrix traps her subjects in the shining sceptre, but it is she who becomes mired.

PredictionText: You will defeat Poporo, the Highest Spire while holding The Stormheart.
Name: The Storm Spire
FlavourText: Cold ocean winds whip across the sharp stones where two yet battle for control.

PredictionText: You will defeat Arakaali, Spinner of Shadows while holding Foxshade.
Name: Dark Instincts
FlavourText: Guided by luck, the fox hunts the spider in absolute shadow.

PredictionText: You will defeat Garukhan, Queen of the Winds while holding Asenath's Mark.
Name: Song of the Sekhema
FlavourText: The Sekhema's whispers fight back the wind, leaving no mark remaining.

PredictionText: You will defeat Eater of Souls while holding Honourhome.
Name: Honour Held
FlavourText: A lone soul escapes the Eater with their honour held firm.

PredictionText: You will defeat Eater of Souls while holding Malachai's Simula.
Name: The Nightmare Awakens
FlavourText: The Eater has his final meal, and the Soulless One awakens.

PredictionText: You will defeat Xixic, High Necromancer while holding Sidhebreath.
Name: WIP
FlavourText: WIP

PredictionText: You will defeat Barthol, the Pure while holding The Ignomon.
Name: Blind Faith
FlavourText: Two sides, light and dark, collide, and leave all but one blind.

PredictionText: You will defeat Hector Titucius, Eternal Servant while holding The Magnate.
Name: The Great Mind of the North
FlavourText: The Eternal servant bathes in his own blood, and a master tactician is born.

PredictionText: You will defeat Boulderback while holding The Magnate.
Name: The Great Leader of the North
FlavourText: The boulder is crushed atop the hill, letting the great leader's people pass.

PredictionText: You will defeat Glace while holding Bloodboil.
Name: Cold Blooded Fury
FlavourText: Winter weaves the cannibal's cold fury until his blood boils over.

PredictionText: You will defeat The Dishonoured Queen while holding Hyrri's Bite.
Name: A Dishonourable Death
FlavourText: The dishonoured niece of the king is decisively laid to rest by her own bite.

PredictionText: You will defeat Piety the Empyrean while holding Dreadarc.
Name: Burning Dread
FlavourText: The Empyrian faces her dread and perishes; her arc now complete.

PredictionText: You will defeat Visceris while holding Goredrill.
Name: Crimson Hues
FlavourText: The ruins hide an artist whose own crimson ink coats the stone.

PredictionText: You will defeat Litanius, the Black Prayer while holding Geofri's Baptism.
Name: Black Devotion
FlavourText: The Black Prayer falls silent in the face of the Archbishop's shimmering devotion.

PredictionText: You will defeat Fragment of Winter while holding Cameria's Maul.
Name: Cold Greed
FlavourText: Avarice turns the heart as cold as a fragment of Winter itself.

PredictionText: You will defeat Skullbeak while holding Redbeak.
Name: The Dreaded Rhoa
FlavourText: The rhoa's rage builds and boils over; a feeling of dread envelops the crimson beak.

PredictionText: You will defeat The Steel Soul while holding The Dancing Dervish.
Name: Dance of Steel
FlavourText: A soul of steel shatters, and a spinning shard joins the eternal dance.

PredictionText: You will defeat Jorus, Sky's Edge while holding Eclipse Solaris.
Name: Blinding Light
FlavourText: The light fades from one source but grows in another, blinding those who approach.

PredictionText: You will defeat Tyrant while holding Iron Heart.
Name: Battle Hardened
FlavourText: The eager warrior meets the Tyrant in battle. Outmatched and outwitted; he uses his strength to best his foe.

PredictionText: You will defeat Tolman, the Exhumer while holding Chober Chaber.
Name: Faith Exhumed
FlavourText: The lost lover returns, but faith releases him from his service.

PredictionText: You will defeat The Cleansing Light while holding Matua Tupuna.
Name: The Mentor
FlavourText: One falls, but another rises to lead.

PredictionText: You will defeat Pagan Bishop of Agony while holding Geofri's Crest.
Name: The Bishop's Legacy
FlavourText: The crest becomes a crown when placed upon the Bishop's brow.
